[4] Cholera - India (Maharashtra State): 2011
Date: Fri 8 Jun 2012
Source: Daily News and Analysis (DNA) [edited]
http://www.dnaindia.com/pune/report_cholera-claimed-79-lives-in-pune-in-2011_1699822


In 2011, 79 people died due to cholera and 28 due to malnutrition in Pune. These shocking facts came to light through a right to information (RTI) query.

RTI activist Vihar Durve filed the query and received its reply from PMC's [Pune Municipal Corporation] birth and death registration section, stating that a total of 25 049 people died within PMC limits in 2011. Of these, cholera, an infectious disease that is notifiable, claimed 79 lives, according to the RTI reply. These trends are seen in previous years too. The 2010 records show 24 deaths due to cholera, while the 2009 records peg cholera deaths alone at 468.

[byline: Alifiya Khan]

